Follow The Post’s coverage of the latest news and memorable performances from the Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival in California. Headliner Harry Styles capped night one off with a legendary guest performance from the one-and-only Shania Twain. The pair sang Twain’s iconic hit single “Man, I Feel Like A Woman,” and it’s safe to say the crowd just couldn’t get enough. Following their performance, Styles spoke of his full-circle moment performing with the country superstar. The singer remembered being in the car with his mom as a little boy, with Twain’s song on full blast. “Shania Twain taught me to sing,” Styles told the Coachella crowd. “She also taught me that men are trash.” Other surprise appearances kept the Coachella crowd on its feet! Night one saw the likes of Justin Bieber and Snoop Dogg join forces with Daniel Caesar and Anitta respectively. Big Sean also wowed the crowd, bringing on rapper YG and singer Jhene Aiko, who also happens to be his girlfriend. Can’t wait to see what insane performances Saturday will bring!